# General Guidelines
- Project language is Java
- Use SLF4J for logging
- Always add documentation when creating new functions and classes
- Use early returns when possible
- Follow standard best code practices

# Code Style
- Use 4 spaces for indentation
- Use camelCase for variable names


# Testing
- Use JUnit 5 for testing
- Write unit tests for all new functions and classes
- Write integration tests for all new functions and classes

# Documentation
- Use Javadoc for documentation
- Document all public functions and classes

# Version Control
- Use Git for version control
- Use semantic versioning

# Project Structure
- Use Maven for project management
- Use src/main/java for source code
- Use src/test/java for test code
- Use src/main/resources for resources
- Use src/test/resources for test resources

# Build
- Use Maven for building
- Use Maven for running
